# module lang

Renders the runtime and language section header. lang and deps together form one prompt section — lang opens the `## [ENVIRONMENT RUNTIME & LANGUAGE]` header and contributes the target specification; deps renders the dependency whitelist as a sub-block beneath it.

# entity Output

```markdown
## [ENVIRONMENT RUNTIME & LANGUAGE]

Write all code strictly targeting the following language specification. Apply the correct module syntax, standard library APIs, and runtime-specific idioms throughout. Do not use syntax, features, or tools that do not belong to this target.

{{body}}
```

# rule

- lang blocks carry no name. A name field on a lang block is a PARSE_ERROR.
- An empty body is a PARSE_ERROR.
- The compiler renders lang first, then deps immediately after. Together they form one visual section in the prompt — the `##` header belongs to lang, the `###` sub-header belongs to deps.
- When multiple lang blocks arrive across cascade levels, only the most specific one is passed to this template.
